    <scopecontent id="aspace_hzc210403n520as34301801344745">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>A 2-page typed letter from Robert Henri in Ireland to Horn, 1927, advising him to study with George Luks or John Sloan, commenting on children as painting subjects, reminding him that the "best...designs are extremely simple," and recommending that he read Henri's book, The Art Spirit.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <altformavail id="aspace_hzc210403n530as45428862842085">
